Kenya Institute of Management held its annual Company of the Year Awards (COYA) at Safari Park Hotel on Friday evening. It seeks to recognise performance of companies for purposes of benchmarking them against global businesses. Crown Paints emerged winner of the COYA award while Beta Healthcare CEO Sanjay Advani was the CEO of the year. ICT cabinet secretary Joe Mucheru was the chief guest and joined others in attendance including KIM executive director David Muturi ICPAK chief executive Patrick Ngumi.